
* ================================================================================
* Model: Real Transformer (T-Model with Leakage & Resistance)
* Description: Models a practical transformer with winding resistances, 
*              magnetizing inductance, and leakage (via coupling < 1).
* Ports: P1, P2 (Primary), S1, S2 (Secondary)
*        Pm, Sm (Internal nodes - see note below)
* Note: Standard SPICE requires all internal nodes to be in the port list. 
*       Connect Pm and Sm to dummy nets (e.g., net_Pm, net_Sm) in your schematic.
* ================================================================================ 
.subckt Transformer P1 P2 S1 S2  PARAMS: 
+ Np=1000 Ns=100
+ Lm=100H
+ Rp=1
+ Rs=0.1
+ Kc=0.999

* Calculate turns ratio and referred secondary inductance
.param RATIO={Np/Ns}
.param Ls_val={Lm*(Ns/Np)^2}

* Winding Resistances
Rp1 P1 Pm {Rp}
Rs1 S1 Sm {Rs}

* Magnetizing/Leakage Inductances
Lp Pm P2 {Lm}
Ls Sm S2 {Ls_val}

* Magnetic Coupling (Kc must be < 1.0 to avoid singular matrix errors)
K1 Lp Ls {Kc}

.ends Transformer

* ===============================================================================
* Model: Ideal Transformer (Behavioral Model)
* Description: Models a 100% ideal transformer using behavioral sources.
*              No leakage, no resistance, infinite magnetizing inductance.
* Ports: P1, P2 (Primary), S1, S2 (Secondary)
*        Px (Internal sensing node)
* ==============================================================================
.subckt IdealTransformer P1 P2 S1 S2  PARAMS: Np=1000 Ns=100

* Turns ratio (N = Np/Ns)
.param N={Np/Ns}

* Zero-volt voltage source to sense primary current
Vsen P1 Px 0

* Primary Voltage = N * Secondary Voltage
E1 Px P2 VALUE={N*V(S1,S2)}

* Secondary Current = -N * Primary Current (Power conservation & dot convention)
F1 S1 S2 Vsen {-N}

.ends IdealTransformer

* =============================================================================
* Model: Mutual Inductor (Coupled Inductors)
* Description: Simple coupled inductors without ideal transformer scaling.
* Ports: P1, P2 (Inductor 1), S1, S2 (Inductor 2)
* Note: The 'K' parameter is the coupling coefficient (0 <= K <= 1), 
*       NOT the mutual inductance in Henries.
* ============================================================================
.subckt MutualInductor P1 P2 S1 S2 PARAMS:
+ Lp=7H
+ Ls=0.02286H
+ K=0.999

Lp P1 P2 {Lp}
Ls S1 S2 {Ls}

* K statement requires coupling coefficient (k), not mutual inductance (M)
K1 Lp Ls {K}

.ends MutualInductor

* ===================================================================================
* ================== USAGE EXAMPLES =================================================
* ===================================================================================
* 
* 1. Real Transformer Usage:
*    X1 P1 P2 S1 S2 net_Pm net_Sm Transformer PARAMS: Np=1000 Ns=100 Lm=100H Kc=0.99
*    (Note: 'net_Pm' and 'net_Sm' are dummy nets required by SPICE syntax).
*
* 2. Ideal Transformer Usage:
*    X2 P1 P2 S1 S2 net_Px IdealTransformer PARAMS: Np=10 Ns=1
*    (Note: 'net_Px' is a dummy net for the internal current sensing node).
*
* 3. Mutual Inductor Usage:
*    X3 N1 N2 N3 N4 MutualInductor PARAMS: Lp=10u Ls=10u K=0.95
*
* Dot Convention Note: 
* For all models, the dot convention is assumed as:
* Primary: Dot at P1. Secondary: Dot at S1.
* ===================================================================================
